race.comment: JULEP (8) is a very well-bred filly by Wootton Bassett out of Full Of Spirit who debuts for the Freedman yard. She's jumped out fairly but this is a very winnable maiden against some well-exposed types and she should take beating for the top yard, especially given the main danger has been scratched. PLEASE ME DO (6) is knocking on the door having placed in her past two. The run two back at Bendigo in a tougher maiden reads well. Strong hope in a winnable race. APPLE EYES (7) faded late at Albury on debut but will be better for it and could give a sight. BRILLIANT BEAGLE (5) is going okay and a place chance.
